    <h2>The arc</h2>

    <p>Each thinker responds to what broke in the previous step. Read top to bottom — the prior answer always generated the next problem.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Thinker</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400">says</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Bacon</td><td class="text-gray-400">observe, don't speculate.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Descartes</td><td class="text-gray-400">doubt everything, rebuild from certainty.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Hume</td><td class="text-gray-400">your observations don't prove anything.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Mill</td><td class="text-gray-400">here's how to extract causes anyway.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Boole</td><td class="text-gray-400">logic is algebra, make it mechanical.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Chamberlin</td><td class="text-gray-400">hold multiple hypotheses or you'll fool yourself.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Popper</td><td class="text-gray-400">you can't prove a theory, only disprove it.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Kuhn</td><td class="text-gray-400">scientists don't actually work that way.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Meehl</td><td class="text-gray-400">more data should make tests harder; in soft psychology it makes them easier. The paradox that predicted the replication crisis by forty years.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Feynman</td><td class="text-gray-400">the first principle is that you must not fool yourself.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Pearl</td><td class="text-gray-400">here is the notation for asking what would have happened if you had reached in and changed something.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Ioannidis</td><td class="text-gray-400">you're fooling yourself.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Mayo</td><td class="text-gray-400">here's how to stop.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Gwern</td><td class="text-gray-400">any method can be gamed, so publish the trail. He calls it <em>long content</em>.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p>Gwern's response is procedural: discipline the researcher. Shafer, Vovk, Grünwald, and Ramdas push at a different layer: the evidence measure itself. The Fisherian apparatus asked "how surprised should I be under the null?" That question is fragile under optional stopping and hard to compose without bespoke corrections (alpha-spending, group-sequential designs, Bonferroni). E-values ask "how much would I bet against the null?" instead. The composition rules and anytime guarantees fall out of one supermartingale inequality, in the constructions where the bets chain validly. Two responses to the same crisis at different layers: discipline (Gwern, Mayo, open-science reforms) and machinery (SAVI). The machinery has its own lineage older than the crisis: Ville's 1939 inequality, Wald's 1947 sequential analysis, the Robbins–Siegmund line of the 1960s. All three ran parallel to Fisher's fixed-horizon view for decades. SAVI is the modern consolidation of that parallel tradition, not a sudden invention prompted by Ioannidis. Neither layer subsumes the other.</p>

    <p>Each thinker responds to a failure of the previous method. The failures are the interesting part.</p>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 mb-8"/>

    <h2>Works</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Work</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">What it changed</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400"></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/bacon-1620/">Bacon 1620</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Replaced Aristotelian deduction with systematic observation. Gave us <em>induction</em>.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/bacon-1620/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/descartes-1637/">Descartes 1637</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Doubt everything, rebuild from certainty. Decompose, solve from simplest to complex.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/descartes-1637/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/hume-1739/">Hume 1739</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">No amount of observation proves the next instance. Killed the certainty Descartes promised.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/hume-1739/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/mill-1843/">Mill 1843</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Five methods for extracting causes. Vary one thing, hold the rest constant.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/mill-1843/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/boole-1854/">Boole 1854</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Reduced logic to algebra. Made reasoning computable. Every <code>if/then/and/or</code> descends from this.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/boole-1854/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/peirce-1878/">Peirce 1878</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Added abduction: inference to the best explanation. The meaning of a concept is its practical consequences.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/peirce-1878/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/chamberlin-1890/">Chamberlin 1890</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Hold multiple hypotheses or your favorite will blind you. Five pages that still fix confirmation bias.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/chamberlin-1890/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/fisher-1935/">Fisher 1935</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Randomization, significance tests, ANOVA. Built the machinery that modern science runs on.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/fisher-1935/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/popper-1934/">Popper 1934</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">You can't prove a theory, only disprove it. Falsifiability as the line between science and everything else.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/popper-1934/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/kuhn-1962/">Kuhn 1962</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Science doesn't accumulate. It breaks and rebuilds. Paradigm shifts happen when anomalies pile up.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/kuhn-1962/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/platt-1964/">Platt 1964</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Strong inference: alternative hypotheses, crucial experiments, repeat. Why some fields move faster.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/platt-1964/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/meehl-1967/">Meehl 1967</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Methodological paradox: more data makes directional nulls easier to reject. The crud factor. NHST for soft psychology is a category error, not a technique to fix.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/meehl-1967/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/feynman-1974/">Feynman 1974</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Cargo cult science. The first principle is that you must not fool yourself, and you are the easiest person to fool.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/feynman-1974/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/pearl-2000/">Pearl 2000</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Causality. The do-operator, the causal hierarchy, and the calculus that turns "is this question answerable from observational data?" from a judgment call into a decision procedure.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/pearl-2000/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/ioannidis-2005/">Ioannidis 2005</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Why most published research findings are false. The replication crisis, diagnosed before it had a name.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/ioannidis-2005/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/mayo-2018/">Mayo 2018</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Severe testing: a test only confirms if it had a real chance of catching you being wrong.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/mayo-2018/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/integrity/">Gwern 2010→</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Long content: any method can be Goodharted, so publish the full trail — data, nulls, revisions — and let anyone audit it.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/integrity/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/self-experiment/">Gwern 2010→</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">The self-experiment: Fisher's randomization at n=1. Self-blinding, power analysis, and published nulls — without the institution.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/self-experiment/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/registered-prediction/">Gwern 2010→</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Registered prediction: assign a probability, set a deadline, publish it, score it. Falsification operationalized.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/registered-prediction/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/shafer-2021/">Shafer 2021</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Testing by betting. Systematized the betting interpretation of probability for hypothesis testing — if Skeptic can grow $1 into $20 wagering against the null, that ratio is the evidence.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/shafer-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/ramdas-2023/">Ramdas et al. 2023</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Game-theoretic statistics, surveyed and named: SAVI. Consolidates two decades of work on e-values, test supermartingales, and confidence sequences into one framework with worked examples for the standard tests.</td><td><a href="/reading/scientific-method/ramdas-2023/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300"><a href="/the-prereg-checklist">Audit checklist</a></td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Twenty-two questions from all of the above, compressed into a pre-registration checklist. Walk through before registering.</td><td><a href="/the-prereg-checklist" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔬</a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2>Vocabulary we inherited</h2>

    <p>Every word in this table was coined or formalized by someone on the list above. We use them without thinking about the argument that produced them.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Term</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Source</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400">What it settled</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Induction</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Bacon</td><td class="text-gray-400">Generalize from observations, don't deduce from axioms</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Method of doubt</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Descartes</td><td class="text-gray-400">Accept nothing without evidence</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Problem of induction</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Hume</td><td class="text-gray-400">Observation never proves necessity</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Method of difference</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Mill</td><td class="text-gray-400">Vary one thing, hold the rest constant</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Boolean logic</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Boole</td><td class="text-gray-400">Reasoning is algebra</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Abduction</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Peirce</td><td class="text-gray-400">Inference to the best explanation</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Null hypothesis, p-value</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Fisher</td><td class="text-gray-400">Quantify how surprised you should be</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Type I/II error, power</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Neyman-Pearson</td><td class="text-gray-400">Hypothesis testing as decision procedure</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Falsifiability</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Popper</td><td class="text-gray-400">The line between science and non-science</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Paradigm shift</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Kuhn</td><td class="text-gray-400">Science breaks and rebuilds, it doesn't just accumulate</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Strong inference</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Platt</td><td class="text-gray-400">Design experiments that exclude alternatives</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Crud factor / methodological paradox</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Meehl</td><td class="text-gray-400">In soft science everything correlates with everything, so rejecting the nil null carries almost no information about a theory</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Severe testing</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Mayo</td><td class="text-gray-400">A test confirms only if it could have caught you being wrong</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Do-operator: do(X)</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Pearl</td><td class="text-gray-400">Notation for intervention. Distinguishes "what is correlated with X" from "what would happen if I forced X"</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Causal hierarchy</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Pearl</td><td class="text-gray-400">Three rungs (seeing, doing, imagining); each needs strictly more than the rung below</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Long content</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Gwern</td><td class="text-gray-400">Publish the full trail — data, nulls, revisions — so the method can't be Goodharted</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Registered prediction</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Gwern</td><td class="text-gray-400">Assign a probability, set a deadline, score it. Falsification with a timestamp.</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">E-value</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Vovk &amp; Wang</td><td class="text-gray-400">Evidence measure with expectation ≤ 1 under the null; multiplies into a valid e-value when chained as a sequential test</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Anytime-valid inference</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Ramdas et al.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Statistical guarantees that hold at any stopping time, not just pre-specified ones</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Test supermartingale</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Shafer</td><td class="text-gray-400">A wealth process whose conditional expectation never increases under the null; its value at any stopping time is a valid e-value</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2>Failures that drove the next step</h2>

    <p>The collection reads differently when you see what broke.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Failure</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">What broke</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400">What it produced</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Aristotelian physics</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Deduction from first principles without observation</td><td class="text-gray-400">Bacon's inductive method</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Phlogiston theory</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Fit the data until Lavoisier weighed the air</td><td class="text-gray-400">Quantitative experiment over plausible narrative</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Luminiferous aether</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Michelson-Morley found nothing. The most productive null result in history.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Einstein's relativity; Kuhn's paradigm shifts</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Eugenics</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Fisher's statistics weaponized by ideology. Sound method, monstrous application.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Research ethics, informed consent, institutional review</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Lysenko affair</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Political authority overriding evidence. Soviet genetics destroyed for decades.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Scientific autonomy as a value worth defending</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Cargo cult science</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Form without substance. Rituals of method without the honesty.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Feynman's integrity principle</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Correlation as causation</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Hormone replacement therapy and heart disease, dietary fat and mortality, vitamin supplementation and almost everything. Decades of observational findings reported as treatment effects.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Neyman's potential outcomes (1923, rediscovered by Rubin 1974), Pearl's do-calculus, and the design-based credibility revolution in econometrics</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Replication crisis</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">P-hacking, publication bias, garden of forking paths</td><td class="text-gray-400">Pre-registration, open data, Mayo's severe testing</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Goodharting the method</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Pre-registration gamed, severity selectively reported. The form of rigor without the trail.</td><td class="text-gray-400">Long content, registered prediction</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Replication crisis (statistical)</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Fixed-horizon p-values are fragile under optional stopping and hard to compose without bespoke corrections. Workarounds exist (alpha-spending, group-sequential designs); they're paid for in power and pre-specification.</td><td class="text-gray-400">E-values and SAVI: an alternative evidence framework where anytime validity and sequential composition fall out of one supermartingale inequality</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2>The protocol</h2>

    <p>Each step exists because someone on the timeline proved it was necessary.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Step</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">What you do</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400">Who established it</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Pre-register</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Write down your hypothesis, your analysis plan, and what would disprove you. Before you see the data.</td><td class="text-gray-400"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/popper-1934/">Popper</a>, <a href="/reading/scientific-method/mayo-2018/">Mayo</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Red-team to convergence</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Generate alternative hypotheses. Design experiments that discriminate between them. Keep generating until you can't anymore.</td><td class="text-gray-400"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/chamberlin-1890/">Chamberlin</a>, <a href="/reading/scientific-method/platt-1964/">Platt</a></td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Work log frequently</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Record observations as they happen. Version your drafts. Tag your confidence. The log is the evidence that you didn't backfill.</td><td class="text-gray-400"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/bacon-1620/">Bacon</a>, <a href="/reading/scientific-method/integrity/">Gwern</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-3 pl-0 text-gray-300">Publish all</td><td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">The positives, the nulls, the embarrassing stuff, the code. A curated trail can be Goodharted. A complete one can't.</td><td class="text-gray-400"><a href="/reading/scientific-method/feynman-1974/">Feynman</a>, <a href="/reading/scientific-method/integrity/">Gwern</a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

